{
  "_readme": [
    "Hand-curated overrides for `generate_spec_enumeration`.",
    "",
    "`repairs` maps a string the HGVS spec marks invalid to the canonical form",
    "the spec ITSELF states, on the cited line. Every entry is transcribed",
    "verbatim from the pinned submodule; nothing here is inferred. When the spec",
    "forbids a form without naming a replacement (`c.52insT` is 'ambiguous';",
    "`g.123dup6` is explicitly 'not clear whether ... g.123_128dup or",
    "g.124_129dup'), the entry is omitted rather than guessed.",
    "",
    "Keys are the verbatim spec string; values are the repaired form INCLUDING",
    "the default accession `prefix::DEFAULTS` prepends to a bare fragment",
    "(c -> NM_004006.2, r -> NM_004006.3, g -> NC_000023.11, p -> NP_003997.1),",
    "since the row asserts `normalize(target) == repaired`.",
    "",
    "`requires_reference: true` marks a repair whose evaluation needs real",
    "reference bases (3'-rule shifting, repeat-to-dup collapse, residue",
    "identities). Those rows are emitted for the record but the hermetic driver",
    "does not assert them.",
    "",
    "`normative_level` is RFC 2119 as the spec words it: 'is not correct' /",
    "'not allowed' / 'can not be' -> must; 'the recommendation is not to' /",
    "'should not be used' -> should. Only `must` rows may ever hard-fail."
  ],
